      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 183: The new raw-value listener decodes every received DeviceAnnouncement while holding mutex_. This can unnecessarily block unrelated presence queries/listener updates, especially because the callback may receive multiple values and also logs decode failures in the locked section. Consider decoding and validating the values before taking mutex_, then only mutate deviceValues under the lock.\n\n```suggestion\nstd::vector\u003cstd::pair\u003cdht::PkId, dht::Value::Id\u003e\u003e decodedValues;\ndecodedValues.reserve(values.size());\nfor (const auto\u0026 value : values) {\n    try {\n        auto dev \u003d dht::Value::unpack\u003cDeviceAnnouncement\u003e(*value);\n        if (!dev.pk) {\n            JAMI_WARNING(\"PresenceManager: Received DeviceAnnouncement without public key for {}\", h.toString());\n            continue;\n        }\n        decodedValues.emplace_back(dev.pk-\u003egetLongId(), value-\u003eid);\n    } catch (const std::exception\u0026 e) {\n        JAMI_WARNING(\"PresenceManager: Failed to decode DeviceAnnouncement {} for {}: {}\",\n                     value-\u003eid,\n                     h.toString(),\n                     e.what());\n    }\n}\n\n{\n    std::lock_guard lock(mutex_);\n    // update deviceValues from decodedValues\n}\n```",
